HEADWORD: Flowery
<hw>Flow"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of
flowers; abounding with blossoms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Highly embellished with figurative language; florid;
<as>as, a <ex>flowery</ex> style</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>The flowery kingdom</b></col>, <cd>China.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flowery-kirtled</ent>⟦br⟧
